commitResults.messageTitle: Rename project to HaBot. Added Greet and Bye
commitResults.messageBody:
(a) Changed bot name to HaBot
(b) Implemented an initial skeletal version
Improve the skeletal version so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add storeMessage to store user input and display with 'list'
commitResults.messageBody: Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enable marks as done or not done with stored value as Task
commitResults.messageBody: Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.

commitResults.messageTitle: Added 3 types of tasks: ToDos, Events, Deadlines
commitResults.messageBody:
Add support for tracking three types of tasks:

1. ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park
2. Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm
3. Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time
e.g., (a) team project meeting 2/10/2019 2-4pm (b) orientation week 4/10/2019 to 11/10/2019
Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of the chatbot
